<h2 id="adding-a-cms">Adding a Content Management System</h2>
<p>ZeroPoint's well-structured content is great for "headless", git-based CMS projects like <a href="https://decapcms.org/">Decap CMS</a> (formerly Netlify CMS) and <a href="http://sveltiacms.app/">Sveltia CMS</a>. These CMSes offer useful feature sets, community support, and scale well.</p>
<p>This example recommends a Git-based CMS like DecapCMS or Sveltia, because they're free, open-source, and don't require an additional server. These CMSes communicate directly with Git, and trigger your existing build and deployment process, keeping everything, even your content, in version control.</p>
<p>To add one of these content management systems to your ZeroPoint site, follow these steps:</p>

<ol class="steps">
  <li>
    <h3 id="create-cms-files">Create two files</h3>
    <p>Adding Decap CMS or Sveltia to ZeroPoint is as simple as adding two files to your project. Both CMSes use a cross-compatible yaml-formatted configuration file, so switching between CMSes is straightforward. Feel free to try both!</p>
    <p>Decap CMS and Sveltia both run in the web browser, requiring no additional server infrastructure. Each authenticates users via GitHub.</p>
    <p>Add <code>admin.yml</code> and <code>config.yml</code> to your <code>content/admin</code> directory.</p>

    <ol>
      <li>
        <h4><code>content/admin/admin.yml</code></h4>
